defaultIn the past English Heritage picked up intelligence and undertook limited horizon scanning and foresight exercises. This happened in an ad-hoc way and there were no mechanisms for collating the intelligence or considering and acting 
defaultupon the foresight or horizon scanning. 
default More recently we have sought to recognise and integrate this work into our future work.
default&#xa0;
default3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn 2011 English Heritage launched the National Heritage Protection Plan (NHPP) which 
defaultis a major strategy that identifies those
default parts of England’s Heritage that matter to people most and are at greatest risk – and then concentrates efforts on saving them
default.
default The plan recognises that t
defaulthere are many public, commercial and voluntary organisations that ensure our heritage is cared for, 
defaultappreciated and enjoyed.
default  
defaultAt the heart of the Plan is a clear set of priorities about what matters and what is in danger of being lost
default and where opportunities exist
default.
default 
defaultThese were identified following a widespread public consultation which is repeated every y
defaultear to ensure the Plan remains up-to-date and relevant to changing circumstances.
